noteParagraph.text: This sub-class covers equipment for the care and culture of all living creatures except human beings, and for obtaining their products, unless provided for elsewhere, e.g. milking , shoeing animals , veterinary devices , culture of bacteria or the like .

titlePart.text: Animal husbandry in general, especially cattle-raising
Housing for domestic or laboratory animals
Devices for use in keeping domestic animals, e.g. fittings in housings, dog beds
Devices for fastening animals, e.g. halters, toggles, neck-bars, chain fastenings
Arrangements for simultaneously releasing several animals

titlePart.entryReference: devices for impeding movement of animals

titlePart.text: Grids for preventing cattle from straying
Feeding devices for stock or game
Watering equipment for stock or game
Devices for grooming or caring of animals, e.g. curry-combs
Protection against weather conditions or insects
Devices for taming animals, e.g. nose-rings, hobbles
Devices for overturning animals in general
Devices for impeding passage through fencing
Devices for assisting or preventing mating
Leads or collars, e.g. for dogs
Testing, cleaning, stamping, or grading eggs
Feeding or drinking appliances for poultry or other birds

titlePart.entryReference: investigating or analizing eggs, e.g. by candling
sorting according to weight in general

titlePart.text: Other aviculture appliances, e.g. devices for determining whether a bird is about to lay
Construction or arrangement of frames for honeycombs
Other details of beehives, e.g. ventilating devices, entrances to hives, guards, partitions, bee escapes
Appliances for treating beehives or parts thereof, e.g. for cleaning or disinfecting
Feeding or drinking appliances for bees

Culture of fish, mussels, crayfish, lobsters, sponges, pearls, etc.
titlePart.entryReference: harvesting oysters, mussels, sponges or the like

titlePart.text: Receptacles for live fish, e.g. aquaria
